==Use==
[[File:Italy cockade.svg|thumb|right|The national [[cockade]] of Italy.]]
The national colours are specified in the [[Constitution of Italy]] to be used on the [[Flag of Italy]], a vertical [[Tricolour (flag)|tricolour flag]] of green, white, and red.{{sfn|La Costituzione}}{{sfn|Constitution of the Italian Republic}} It is also used on the [[cockade]], another of the [[national symbols of Italy]]. Its use of the national colours was the antecedent for its use in the flag.{{sfn|Biblioteca dell'Accademia virgiliana|p=4|ps=...o Bandiera Cispadana di tre colori, verde, bianco e rosso, e che questi tre colori si usino anche nella coccarda cispadana la quale debba portarsi da tutti}}{{sfn|Protonotari|1897|p=239-267 and 676–710}}{{sfn|Murati|1892|p=12–13}}

The [[Flag of Italy#Presidential standard|Presidential Standard of Italy]] is the flag used by the [[President of Italy|President of the Italian Republic]], the nation's [[head of state]]. It is based on the square flag of the Napoleonic Italian Republic, on a field of blue [[Charge (heraldry)|charged]] with the [[Emblem of Italy|coat of arms of Italy]] in gold.{{sfn||Gazzetta Ufficiale della Repubblica Italiana|2000}}

On 31 December 1996, legislation was passed (''legge no. 671'') instituting 7 January as national [[flag day]], known as ''[[Festa del Tricolore]]'', and was published in the Gazzetta Ufficiale della Repubblica Italiana three days later.{{sfn|Gazzetta Ufficiale della Repubblica Italiana|1997}} Its purpose was to celebrate the bicentennial of the establishment of the Italian flag on 7 January 1797.{{sfn|La Repubblica|2013}} The most important of these celebrations is that at the [[Sala del Tricolore (Reggio Emilia)|Sala del Tricolore]] ("Room of the tricolour") in the commune palace of [[Reggio Emilia]], and a solemn changing of the guard at the [[Quirinal Palace]] in Rome, followed by a parade of the [[Corazzieri]] and a brass band fanfare by the [[Carabinieri Cavalry Regiment]].{{sfn|La Repubblica|2013}}

===Sport===
[[File:Scudetto.svg|thumb|right|The ''scudetto'' is worn on jerseys by the team that wins the [[Serie A]] championships]]

In [[Football in Italy|football]], the winners of [[Serie A]] are the [[List of Italian football champions|Italian football champions]], which entitles the winning team to adorn the jersey of each of its players with the ''scudetto'', an [[Escutcheon (heraldry)|escutcheon]] ([[heater shield]]) of the Italian flag, the subsequent season.{{sfn|Lega Nazionale Professionisti: Premiazione scudetto|2012}} The practice was established in 1924, after [[Gabriele D'Annunzio]] had wanted to put a shield flag on the uniforms of Italian military commanders during a [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly match]].{{sfn|Lega Nazionale Professionisti: Premiazione scudetto|2012}} The league operators state that it is "representative of national unity at the level of football".{{sfn|Lega Nazionale Professionisti: Premiazione scudetto|2012|ps=...uno scudetto con i colori della bandiera italiana, rappresentativo dell'unità nazionale a livello calcistico}} The winner of the [[Coppa Italia]] is entitled to adorn its team jersey with a tricolour cockade for the subsequent season.{{sfn|Lega Nazionale Professionisti:Regolamento|2012|loc=section 12.1 Società vincitrice|p=247/700 and Articolo 1}}<!-- the attachment shows the adornment (the cockade) -->

After having played its first two international matches in white in 1910, the [[Italy national football team|men's football team]] announced its new uniform on 31 December 1910, an [[Azure (color)|azure]] shirt with an escutcheon of the Italian colours, and white shorts.{{sfn|Chiesa|2012|loc=[http://www.magliarossonera.it/img_cronistoriadelfootball/gs/3gs.pdf chapter 1910–1912, Azzurri come il cielo]|p=44|ps=Siamo informati che la squadra nazionale avra finalmente una sua propria divisa: una maglia di colore bleu marinaro, con sul petto uno scudo racchiudente i colori italiani}} Widespread opinion was that the blue colour had been chosen as an homage to the [[House of Savoy]] that had previously ruled parts of [[northern Italy]] until the [[Italian unification|nation's unification]].{{sfn|Chiesa|2012|loc=[http://www.magliarossonera.it/img_cronistoriadelfootball/gs/3gs.pdf chapter 1910–1912, Azzurri come il cielo]|p=44}} The uniform was first worn on 6 January 1911 in a match against [[Hungary national football team|Hungary]] in [[Milan]].{{sfn|Chiesa|2012|loc=[http://www.magliarossonera.it/img_cronistoriadelfootball/gs/3gs.pdf chapter 1910–1912, Azzurri come il cielo]|p=44}}

In sport, many men's national teams are known as the ''azzurri'' and women's teams as the ''azzurre'' (meaning "azure"). These include the [[Italy national basketball team|men's basketball]],{{sfn|Federazione Italiana Pallacanestro: Gli azzurri}} [[Italy national football team|men's football]], [[Italy men's national ice hockey team|men's ice hockey]], [[Italy national rugby league team|men's rugby league]], [[Italy national rugby union team|men's rugby union]], and [[Italy men's national volleyball team|men's volleyball]]{{sfn|Federazione Italiana Pallavolo: Azzurri}} teams, and the [[Italy women's national basketball team|women's basketball]],{{sfn|Federazione Italiana Pallacanestro: Le Azzurre}} [[Italy women's national football team|women's football]], [[Italy women's national ice hockey team|women's ice hockey]], and [[Italy women's national volleyball team|women's volleyball]]{{sfn|Federazione Italiana Pallavolo: Azzurre}} teams.

The [[List of international auto racing colors|national auto racing colour]] of Italy is [[rosso corsa]] ("racing red").{{sfn|Bristow|2013|p=7}}

==Other==
[[File:Frecce Tricolori RIAT 2011.JPG|thumb|right|The ''Frecce Tricolori'' with green, white, and red smoke trails]]

The [[Frecce Tricolori]], the [[aerobatics]] demonstration team of the Italian [[Aeronautica Militare]] based at [[Rivolto Air Force Base]], are so named for the green, white, and red smoke trails emitted during performances, representing the national colours.{{sfn|Haberman|1989}}{{sfn|Wings|p=6|ps=the Italians call themselves Frecce Tricolori (and emphasize the title by emitting red, white, and green smoke)}}

The name of  ''Italia Peak'', a [[Summit|peak]] in the [[Elk Mountains (Colorado)|Elk Mountains]] of [[Colorado]] in the [[United States]], is derived from the display on one of its faces, when seen at a distance, of "brilliant red, white and green colors, the national colors of Italy".{{sfn|Ayer|1880|p=211}}{{sfn|Diller|1902|p=145}}{{sfn|Dana|Silliman|1874|p=400}}

